  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HIV AIDS intervention program in Kachin State (Wai Maw)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. PLH leaders will understand the role of leaders and lead the teams properly in their respective areas. 
2. create enabling environment in terms of better response to HIV/AIDS, stigma and discrimination. 
3. PLHs and their families will have improved health, psychological through social economic support provided by the project. 
4.Increased advocacy allows PLHs to live as full community members.
5.PLHs will have increased knowledge of treatment and other services, enhancement of social, psychological and spiritual wellbeing when they participate in peer group meetings. 75% increasing in the number of PLH accessing health services such as STI, TB, hepatitis, ART etc.,
6. 60% PLHs and their partners report regular use of condoms and reduction in risky behaviours amongst PLHs</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Goal:	People living with HIV &amp; AIDS are mobilized and empowered to take the lead in HIV prevention and care programmes in Wai Maw Township in Kachin State.
Objectives:
1.	Empower the PLH network groups through the building of technical capacity in HIV/AIDS interventions and effective management of the program.
2.	Enhance the local capacity in addressing the social and economic challenges, assisting the spread of HIV to reduce stigma and discrimination in community.
3.	Increase involvement of PLH in the community HIV prevention programmes through leading awareness campaigns disseminating proper and accurate knowledge of HIV &amp; AIDS, TB, drug abuse and related issues and focus advocacy with local authorities.
4.	Ensure the overall performance of the activities through the participatory effective M &amp; E and mentoring support.</narrative>
  </description>
